ce:section.ce:para:
The modified Langmuir-Hinshelwood equation governs the kinetics of the photodegradation reaction and determines the photocatalytic activity through apparent rate constant (Kapp) at varying light intensities. Such activity measurements are independent of the concentration of remaining solute and the adsorption extent in dark. The first order kinetics governing the photocatalytic degradation process is represented by the following equation;

                              ln (cₒ / c) = Kapp t

                        where cₒ and c are the initial and the remaining solute concentrations at t = 0 and at irradiation time t, respectively. The ln (cₒ/c) plots with the corresponding irradiation time are shown in Fig. 10B.
